This initialization of data in "result" should happen in the function that's called. I think the forEach loop should be very simple and just do this:
searchResponse.results.forEach(result => {
  if (entityName != null) {
    addEntitySpecificProperties(...);
  } else {
    addGenericEntityProperties(...);
  }
});

That way, only addEntitySpecificProperties cares about selected properties - that concept doesn't exist in addGenericEntityProperties, since we're using a fixed set of columns (I think?).

